---
import '../styles/global.css';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

---
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
		<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=K2D:ital,wght@0,100;0,200;0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;0,800;1,100;1,200;1,300;1,400;1,500;1,600;1,700;1,800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
		<title>Michael Pasimio</title>
	</head>
	<body>
	<Header />
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="hero-text">
			<h1>Michael Vincent Pasimio</h1>
			<p>learning designer, educator, innovator</p>
			<p>based in washington dc</p>
			<div class="orange-line"></div>
			<div class="tagline">
				<p>reimagining education as 
				<br>a public process</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="about">
		<div class="about-content">
			<div class = "aboutSectionTitle">
				<h2>My story</h2>
			</div>
			<div class ="about-text">
				<p>As a student, educator, and learning designer, I am constantly grappling with this tension: is education for individual success or collective flourishing?</p>
				<p>I spent years chasing success, only to find myself isolated, suffocated by the emptiness of my pursuits. I came to realize that the unequal, hyper-individual pursuit of success is tearing our society apart. But the problem is larger than any individual's choices: the very structure of our education system rewards self-interested behavior.</p>		
				<p>I'm dedicated to deconstructing this system of self-interest and rebuilding one that promotes democratic, shared progress.</p>
				<p>In this portfolio, I develop the idea of education as a public process through my writing, research, and projects. If any of this resonates with you, reach out to me. I'd love to talk.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="about-image">
			<img src="/../profile-about-frame.png" alt="a headshot of michael standing behind a podium that says georgetown university" />
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="featured">
		<div class="sectionTitleCenter">
			<h2>The public process</h2>
		</div>
		<p>Click to see an example of each part of the process.</p>
		<div class="featuredWorks">
			<a href="projects/tennis-journey" class="featuredWork">
				<!--  -->
				<h3>1. Connect</h3>
				<p>Build meaningful, local relationships with young people, organizations, and educators.</p>
				<img src="/../tennis-journey-blue.png" alt="Project 1" />
				<p>Checkout my partnership with a local tennis academy</p>
			</a>
			<a href="projects/community-university" class="featuredWork">
				<h3>2. Partner</h3>
				<p>Discuss common challenges, share resources, and co-create solutions</p>
				<img src="/../asu-social-embed.png" alt="Project 2" />
				<p>See how ASU builds partnerships throughout its entire region</p>
			</a>
			<a href= "projects/livingston-college" class="featuredWork">
				<!--   -->
				<h3>3. Rebuild</h3>
				<p>Recreate systems to better meet real, present, shared problems.</p>
				<img src="/../livingston-college.png" alt="Project 3" />
				<p>See how an experimental college in the 70s was designed to address structural racism</p>
			</a>
		</div>
	
	</section>

	<section class="theoryOfChange">
		
		<div class = "theoryOfChangeContainer">
			<div class = "theoryOfChangeText">
				<div class= "theoryOfChangeTitle">
				<h2>My values</h2>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class ="principles">
				<div class="principle">
					<div class="principle-title">
						<button class="expand-btn" aria-label="Expand principle">
							<img src="/expand.png" alt="expand" />
						</button>
						<h3>community building</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="principle-text">A transformative education is one that supplies resources and makes space for people to support meaningful lives and nourish their communities. My educational design work focuses on student voice, mutual ownership, financial sovereignty, and community building.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="principle">
					<div class="principle-title">
						<button class="expand-btn" aria-label="Expand principle">
							<img src="/expand.png" alt="expand" />
						</button>
						<h3>systems thinking</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="principle-text">Education is nested in a web of other complex systems, including housing, labor, and political systems. My design approach takes a broad view and honors complexity while remaining specific and actionable.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="principle">
					<div class="principle-title">
						<button class="expand-btn" aria-label="Expand principle">
							<img src="/expand.png" alt="expand" />
						</button>
						<h3>cyclical processes</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="principle-text">Education is a lifelong process, and every era presents a new wave of problems. I do not expect to perfectly fix anything for anyone in my lifetime, but I do believe that we can always improve and adapt.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="focusAreas">
		<div class="sectionTitleCenter">
			<h2>My work</h2>
		</div>
			<p>I've organized my work around three key reforms. Implementing these reforms will start to transform education into a public process.</p>
		<div class="areas">
			<div class="area pathways" data-category="Rethinking Pathways to Success">
				<h3>Restructure Pathways to Success</h3>
				<p>Redefine the connections between K-12, higher ed, and the workforce.</p>
				<div class="area-dropdown pathwaysDark">See Works ↗︎</div>
			</div>
			<div class="area placeBased" data-category="Place-Based Education">
				<h3>The Anchor Institution Identity</h3>
				<p>Share in local challenges, facilitate conversation, provide research insights, and invest in the regional economy.</p>
				<div class="area-dropdown placeBasedDark">See Works ↗︎</div>
			</div>
			<div class="area techEquity" data-category="Technology and Educational Equity">
				<h3>Technology for Educational Equity</h3>
				<p>The way that a technology is implemented matters as much as the technology itself. It is important to only incorporate technology with a clear framework and goal.</p>
				<div class="area-dropdown techEquityDark">See Works ↗︎</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<Footer />
<script>
	// Handle expand/collapse functionality for principles
	document.querySelectorAll('.principle').forEach(principle => {
		principle.addEventListener('click', function(this: HTMLElement) {
			const img = this.querySelector('img');
			const text = this.querySelector('.principle-text');
			
			if (!text || !img) return;

			const isExpanded = text?.classList.contains('expanded');
			
			if (isExpanded) {
				// Collapse
				text.classList.remove('expanded');
				img.src = '/expand.png';
				img.alt = 'expand';
			} else {
				// Expand
				text.classList.add('expanded');
				img.src = '/collapse.png';
				img.alt = 'collapse';
			}
		});
	});

	// Handle focus area card clicks for routing
	document.querySelectorAll('.area').forEach(area => {
		area.addEventListener('click', function(this: HTMLElement) {
			const category = this.getAttribute('data-category');
			if (category) {
				window.location.href = `/projects?filter=${encodeURIComponent(category)}`;
			}
		});
	});
</script>

	</body>
</html>
